article.headline: Reynolds' 26 help Saint Joseph's (PA) beat Iona 83-58 at Holiday Hoopfest
article.description: — Erik Reynolds II's 26 points helped Saint Joseph's (PA) defeat Iona 83-58 on Saturday night at Holiday Hoopfest.
article.linkText: Reynolds' 26 help Saint Joseph's (PA) beat Iona 83-58 at Holiday Hoopfest
article.story: ELMONT, N.Y. -- — Erik Reynolds II's 26 points helped Saint Joseph's (PA) defeat Iona 83-58 on Saturday night at Holiday Hoopfest. Reynolds shot 7 for 10 (6 for 8 from 3-point range) and 6 of 7 from the free-throw line for the Hawks (9-2). Cameron Brown added 17 points while shooting 6 for 11, including 5 for 9 from beyond the arc, and he also had seven rebounds. Lynn Greer III had 10 points and was 2-of-5 shooting and 6 of 6 from the free-throw line. The Hawks extended their win streak to six games. The Gaels (4-7) were led in scoring by Dylan Saunders, who finished with 16 points. Greg Gordon added 11 points and six rebounds for Iona. Jeremiah Quigley also had nine points, four assists and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
